<apex:page showHeader="false" id="VFP_Sing_PrivacyPolicy" controller="VFC_SingTermsPolicy">
  <style type="text/css">
    .contentbody {
      padding: 22px;
      margin: 0;
      outline: none;
      font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif;
      /*font-size: 14px;*/
      color: #666;
      line-height: 22px;
    }
    h1 {
      font-size: 30px;
      color: #666;
    }
    .divscroll {
      width: 900px;
      height: 1000px;
      overflow: auto; //border-radius: 25px;
      /*background: #669999;*/
      /*text-align: center;*/
      padding: 60px 20px 20px 20px;
      box-shadow: rgb(38, 57, 77) 0px 20px 30px -10px;
    }
    .btn {
      padding: 10px!important;
      width: 150px!important;
      border-radius: 5px!important;
      background: #669999!important;
      color: #fff!important;
      font-size: 14px!important;
      cursor: pointer!important;
    }
    .btn:hover {
      background: #a3c2c2!important;
    }
    .sectionTitle {
      color: #669999;
    }
    .tableBorder, .tableBorder th, .tableBorder td {border-collapse: collapse;
      border:1px solid #666;
      padding-left: 10px;
      padding-right: 10px;
    }
    .tabulation{
      padding-left: 20px;
      text-align: left !important;
      display: block;
    }
  </style>

  <script>
    function ckChange(ckType) {
      var ckName = document.querySelectorAll("input[type='checkbox']");
      var checked = document.getElementById(ckType.id);

      if (checked.checked) {
        for (var i = 0; i < ckName.length; i++) {

          if (!ckName[i].checked) {
            ckName[i].disabled = true;
          } else {
            ckName[i].disabled = false;
          }
        }
      }
      else {
        for (var i = 0; i < ckName.length; i++) {
          ckName[i].disabled = false;
        }
      }
    }
  </script>

  <html>
    <body class="contentbody">
      <center>
        <div class="divscroll">
          <h2>Privacy Policy </h2>

          <span style='text-align: justify;text-justify: inter-word;'>
            <p>AXA Group Operations (“AXA GO”) is a simplified joint-stock company with its registered office at 81, Rue Mstislav
              Rostropovitch, 75017 – Paris, FRANCE.
            </p>

            <p>AXA GO and its affiliates, each acting independently as controller, in accordance with the 2016/679 General Data
              Protection Regulation of the European Parliament and of the Council (“GPDR”), process your personal data in a
              lawful, fair and transparent manner.
            </p>

            <p><b>“Personal data”</b> is any information identifying you or making you identifiable (through indirect means).</p>

            <p>This privacy policy (the “Privacy Policy”) is meant to inform you about:
            <span class="tabulation">
                1. the processing of your Personal data in Contract’in (the type of personal data, the purpose(s) and the period
                of time for which your Personal data is stored),<br/> 
                2. the location of such processing (where your Personal data is processed, third parties who may access it and
                measures taken to protect such transfers),<br/> 
                3. your rights regarding the processing of your Personal data (what you can do with regard to such processing
                and before whom you can file requests or exercise your rights), and<br/> 
                4. where to exercise your rights (points of contact).
            </span></p>

            <p class="sectionTitle"><b>1. The processing – Why we process your Personal data </b></p>

            <p>AXA GO and its affiliates may process the following Personal data for the below purpose(s) in accordance with a
              defined retention period:</p>

              <table class="tableBorder">
                <tr>
                  <th>PROCESSED PERSONAL DATA</th>
                  <th>PURPOSE</th>
                  <th>LEGAL BASIS</th>
                  <th>RETENTION PERIOD</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Full name, professional contact information including your job position, professional email and phone number 
                    and connection data including username, password, IP address, MAC address or work mobile phone identification number.</td>
                  <td>Management of online bidding</td>
                  <td>Legitimate interest </td>
                  <td>3 years for Personal data related to the management of your account.<br/><br/>
                    10 years for Personal data related to the bidding documents.
                  </td>
                </tr>
              </table>

            <p class="sectionTitle"><b>2.	Third parties &amp; Protection – What we do with your data </b></p>

            <p>Your Personal data are transferred for processing, hosting or archiving purposes to the following contractors and 
              service providers established in the following territories, after their security and compliance with data privacy regulations 
              have been assessed and deemed satisfactory:
            </p>

            <table class="tableBorder">
              <tr>
                <th>PROCESSOR</th>
                <th>TERRITORIES WHERE YOUR PERSONAL DATA IS PROCESSED</th>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Salesforce</td>
                <td>France, Germany</td>
              </tr>
            </table>

            <p>AXA GO has signed a data processing agreement with this service provider.</p>

            <p class="sectionTitle"><b>3.	Your rights – What you can do with regard to this processing</b></p>

            <p>You can exercise your right of access, right to rectification, right to erasure, right to restriction of processing and 
              right to object in compliance with applicable data privacy laws at the following email address: 
              <a href="mailto:privacy.axaservices@axa.com">privacy.axaservices@axa.com</a>
            </p>

            <p>You can also contact the data protection authority with jurisdiction over the processing carried out by AXA GO, 
              the French <i>Commission Nationale de l’Informatique et des Libertés</i> (CNIL):
            </p>

            <table class="tableBorder">
              <tr>
                <td>
                    <span style="font-weight: bold">Commission Nationale de l’Informatique et des Libertés</span><br/>
                    3 Place de Fontenoy - TSA 80715<br/>
                    75334 PARIS CEDEX 07<br/>
                    Phone: +33 1 (0) 1 53 73 22 22
                </td>
              </tr>
            </table>

            <apex:form >
              <br/>
              <hr/>
              <p>
                <b>*I acknowledge that I have policy, and do hereby</b>
              </p>
              <apex:pageBlock id="theBlock">
                <table>
                  <td style="padding: 4px ! important;"><label for="request-true">Accept</label></td>
                  <td><apex:inputCheckbox styleClass="checkterms" id="checkterms1" value="{!agree}" onClick="ckChange(this)"/></td>
                  <td style="padding: 4px ! important;"><label for="request-true">Decline</label></td>
                  <td><apex:inputCheckbox styleClass="checkterms" id="checkterms2" value="{!decline}" onClick="ckChange(this)"/></td>
                  </table>
              </apex:pageBlock>
              <center>
                <p>                
                  <apex:commandButton id="btnFinish" styleClass="btn" value="Finish" action="{!processCommandLink}" rerender="dummy">
                    <apex:param name="buttonAction" value="Next_PrivacyPolicy" assignTo="{!buttonAction}"/>
                  </apex:commandButton> 
                </p>
              </center>
            </apex:form>
            <apex:outputPanel id="dummy"/>
          </span>
        </div>
      </center>
    </body>
  </html>
</apex:page>